  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Rohan, I'm your English chat partner. I like tea, by the way — what's your go-to drink when you're studying for the bank exam?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I usually drink tea too, but sometimes coffee. Tea keeps me calm, coffee gives more energy. How about you? Do you like coffee or tea more? By the way, I like to watch *Khel* (football) when I take breaks."
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I like tea too — it just feels right in the afternoon. Football breaks sound like a smart way to rest. What team do you follow most?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I follow Real Madrid mostly, but I also like Barcelona. In India, people love *Mohun Bagan* or *East Bengal*. Do you like football? I think it's the best *khel* in the world."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said, “Real Madrid mostly, but Barcelona” — nice contrast! Football is definitely the most popular khel in many countries. What’s your favourite part of watching it — the goals, the teamwork, or something else?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I like the teamwork the most. When players pass the ball so well, it feels like art. Also, last-minute goals make my heart jump! But sometimes I take photos of my favorite players too. Do you watch any football? Or maybe you like some other *khel* more?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said \"make my heart jump\" — that’s such a vivid way to put it! Teamwork as art is a great image. I don’t watch much football, but I love how passionate people get about it. What gets you most excited when you take photos of players — their expressions or the action?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I take photos mostly for their expressions, like when they smile after scoring a goal. The action shots are cool too, but sometimes they are blurry. I also like to take photos in Bengali movies — the actors look like stars. You know, like *Prosenjit* or *Rituparna*. Do you like movies?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said \"look like stars\" — that’s a perfect phrase! I get that — movie actors do carry that starry charm. Prosenjit and Rituparna are great picks. Do you go to watch them on the big screen or prefer home viewings?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I go to watch Bengali movies on the big screen when they come out — it’s more fun! The sound and everything feels bigger. Sometimes I watch again at home, but not as exciting. Oh, I should get back to study. Talk to you later, Maya!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You said \"more fun\" — and that’s exactly right. Big screens do make everything feel bigger. Take your time with your studies — I’ll be here when you need a quick chat. Talk soon!"
    }
  ],
